version: 1
display_name: PHTN-50-000209 - The Photon operating system must create a home directory for all new local interactive user accounts.
global_description: |-
  If local interactive users are not assigned a valid home directory, there is no place for the storage and control of files they should own.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - PHTN-50-000209
  srg:
    - SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227
  cci:
    - CCI-000366
  nist:
    - CM-6 b
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_photon_5:
    type: custom
    desc: The Photon operating system must create a home directory for all new local interactive user accounts.
    control_id: PHTN-50-000209
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      At the command line, run the following command to verify a home directory is created for all new user accounts:

      # grep '^CREATE_HOME' /etc/login.defs

      Example result:

      CREATE_HOME yes

      If the "CREATE_HOME" option is not set to "yes", is missing or commented out, this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      If local interactive users are not assigned a valid home directory, there is no place for the storage and control of files they should own.
    remediation: |-
      Navigate to and open:

      /etc/login.defs

      Add or update the following line:

      CREATE_HOME yes
